<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Choleric" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Choleric,</orth> 1) irascible: <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.177" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 177</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.302" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 302</bibl>.<lb />2) angry: <cit><quote>a c. word,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 2, 130</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>before you were so c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.68" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 68</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.43" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.177" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 6, 177</bibl>. Followed by <emph>with</emph>: <cit><quote>are you so c. with Eleanor,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.2.51" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 2, 51</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) making irascible: <cit><quote>too c. a meat,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 19</bibl></cit>. 22 (cf. <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.175" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 175</bibl>. 177).
